folder: Irving Avenue & Suydam Place, Brooklyn, NY
text:
Irving Avenue, north side, between Suydam Place and Willoughby Avenue. Occupying the above site is Public School No. 123 (right) and the crowd is gathered outside to partake in Arbor Day exercises. The view is west on Irving Avenue.
MAY BE REPRODUCED  May 5, 1905
